# Azure AI Foundry Voice Live API Configuration
# Copy this file to .env and fill in your values

# Required: Azure AI Foundry resource name
VITE_AZURE_AI_FOUNDRY_RESOURCE=your-resource-name

# Required: Azure Speech/Voice Live API key
VITE_AZURE_SPEECH_KEY=your-api-key-here

# Optional: Avatar configuration (leave commented for voice-only)
# VITE_AVATAR_CHARACTER=lisa
# VITE_AVATAR_STYLE=casual-sitting

# ==============================================================================
# Azure AI Foundry Agent Service Configuration (Optional)
# ==============================================================================
# Use these to connect to a custom agent instead of direct model access
# Agent Service requires user authentication via MSAL (Microsoft Authentication Library)

# Step 1: Register an Azure AD Application
# 1. Go to Azure Portal > Azure Active Directory > App registrations
# 2. Click "New registration"
# 3. Name: "Voice Live Agent Service App"
# 4. Supported account types: Choose appropriate option (usually "Single tenant")
# 5. Redirect URI: Select "Single-page application (SPA)" and enter: http://localhost:3001
# 6. Click "Register"

# Step 2: Configure API Permissions
# 1. In your app registration, go to "API permissions"
# 2. Click "Add a permission" > "APIs my organization uses"
# 3. Search for "Azure AI" or use Application ID: "51bed0f0-4191-45e2-9f39-8cfbb47a0223"
# 4. Select "Delegated permissions"
# 5. Check "user_impersonation" (this provides access to https://ai.azure.com/.default scope)
# 6. Click "Add permissions"
# 7. Click "Grant admin consent" (requires admin privileges)

# Step 3: Copy Configuration Values
# From your app registration overview page:
# VITE_AZURE_CLIENT_ID=your-azure-app-client-id-here
# VITE_AZURE_TENANT_ID=your-azure-tenant-id-here

# Step 4: Configure Agent Service Details
# From your Azure AI Foundry project:
# VITE_AGENT_ID=your-agent-id
# VITE_PROJECT_NAME=your-project-name

# Example values (replace with your actual values):
# VITE_AZURE_CLIENT_ID=12345678-1234-1234-1234-123456789012
# VITE_AZURE_TENANT_ID=87654321-4321-4321-4321-210987654321
# VITE_AGENT_ID=asst_abc123xyz
# VITE_PROJECT_NAME=my-ai-project

# Note: Agent Service authentication happens in the browser via MSAL.
# Users will be prompted to sign in with their Azure AD account when using the Agent Service example.
# The access token is acquired with the scope: https://ai.azure.com/.default
